T1  - Common stock returns in corporate takeover bids: Evidence from interstate bank mergers
AU  - Millon Cornett, Marcia
AU  - De, Sankar
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 15
IS  - 2
SP  - 273
EP  - 295
PY  - 1991
DA  - 1991/04/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(91)90068-W
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669190068W
AB  - Since 1982, a large number of interstate bank mergers have taken place within the legal framework of state statutes passed in response to the Douglas Amendment to the Bank Holding Company Act of 1956. This study investigates stock market reactions to the announcements of the mergers. In contrast to the findings of studies of non-financial mergers, this study documents significant positive announcement period excess returns for both bidding and target banks. The results imply that there may be factors unique to bank mergers that increase bidder returns relative to non-financial mergers. Several possible factors are discussed.
ER  - 

