UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669190072T
AB  - This paper has two purposes. One is to construct a formal model of the determination of and relationships between interest rates on funds with 24-hour, overnight, and intraday terms. The second is to use this model to examine the likely effects of alternative Federal Reserve proposals for addressing the issue of intraday extension of Federal Reserve credit in the form of daylight overdrafts of bank reserve accounts. It is demonstrated that present proposals all entail potentially significant drawbacks for monetary policy.
